<subSubSection id="A454817D2F19D77B70A0A9FA7259236E" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="831D3D4CDBFC48310752D8834BABF99F" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B110C900B69970224CC5C98DDD13F664" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">The specific name refers to the type locality, Xiangzhou Village.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9EA48EA463770DBD128EBD239FF7F9B" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C144801F91701812D5B7FE7ECDB36BC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C6BA6CC7C912CD77CE8BB219152DA72A" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="62F2791EC568C74931ECF2AAC4E5144D" genus="S." lsidName="S. nigra" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="nigra">
<emphasis id="B90288934FA4CC076B9853D53F21C8D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">S. nigra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 by having slit-like copulatory openings (
<emphasis id="F6045B88D85125C0C3CDA7412220BB7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">CO</emphasis>
), but differs by lacking lateral sclerotised margins of copulatory openings (vs. lateral margins sclerotised), touching membranous sacs (vs. separated) and slightly separated spermathecae (vs. touching) (cf. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B4056193D54AE5D600848111A5ED5185" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Stephanopis xiangzhouica sp. nov., female epigyne, holotype. A ventral view B dorsal view. Abbreviations: CO - copulatory opening, FD - fertilisation duct, GA - glandular appendage, MS - membranous sac, SP - spermatheca. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672175" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">13</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="602EA0E43B8D6D147B07AF12A05F5FD6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.2201-4349.71.2019.1698" author="Machado, M" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Australian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="217 - 276" refId="B11" refString="Machado, M, Teixeira, RA, Milledge, GA, 2019. On the Australian bark crab spider genus Stephanopis: taxonomic review and description of seven new species (Araneae: Thomisidae: Stephanopinae). Records of the Australian Museum 71 (6): 217 - 276, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3853/j.2201-4349.71.2019.1698" title="On the Australian bark crab spider genus Stephanopis: taxonomic review and description of seven new species (Araneae: Thomisidae: Stephanopinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.2201-4349.71.2019.1698" volume="71" year="2019">Machado et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 37C, D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FDAF1C305C89E31F1EBF17263F0468CB" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="CA3D1D6E0E0AA7F0DC745B18C7D68977" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4D3F67B61893D55AC93BFAD72062DAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="02B6B4A0599C725CD92E150FE97B2C6C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="943827497FC6D99097556C97F286BA4B" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Stephanopis xiangzhouica sp. nov., female holotype. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C cephalic part, dorsal view D left chelicera, mesal view E left leg I, prolateral view F patella I, prolateral view G abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D, F), 0.5 mm (E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672174" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">12A, B</figureCitation>
. Total length 5.48. Carapace: 2.78 long, 2.96 wide, covered with numerous strong, short, radially diverging setae and dense short plumose setae, with three rows of short strong setae along midline. Eye sizes and interdistances (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="29018B957556062A89B02D361F7306B5" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Stephanopis xiangzhouica sp. nov., female holotype. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C cephalic part, dorsal view D left chelicera, mesal view E left leg I, prolateral view F patella I, prolateral view G abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D, F), 0.5 mm (E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672174" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">12C</figureCitation>
): AME 0.04, ALE 0.07, PME 0.05, PLE 0.06, AME-AME 0.07, AME-ALE 0.04, PME-PME 0.12, PME-PLE 0.13, AME-PME 0.22, AME-PLE 0.31, ALE-ALE 0.25, PLE-PLE 0.57, ALE-PLE 0.14. MOA 0.26 long, front width 0.13, back width 0.24. Chelicerae (Fig. D) with three promarginal (middle largest, distal and proximal smaller) and two retromarginal (proximal large, distal very small) teeth, and numerous macrosetae anteriorly. Endites 2 
<normalizedToken id="88AF52FD3030E788181983D7B5C1503C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide, ectal part without distinct constriction. Labium wider than long. Sternum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F9E107849A0CA7AB607844E04DF067E9" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Stephanopis xiangzhouica sp. nov., female holotype. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C cephalic part, dorsal view D left chelicera, mesal view E left leg I, prolateral view F patella I, prolateral view G abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D, F), 0.5 mm (E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672174" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">12B</figureCitation>
) oval with short dense macrosetae. Abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FC6AE0FDABA55E826D2FCACBAE6FB119" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Stephanopis xiangzhouica sp. nov., female holotype. A habitus, dorsal view B same, ventral view C cephalic part, dorsal view D left chelicera, mesal view E left leg I, prolateral view F patella I, prolateral view G abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B), 0.1 mm (C, D, F), 0.5 mm (E, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672174" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">12A, B, G</figureCitation>
): 2.79 long, 2.94 wide, pentagonal with pair of latero-posterior horns; dorsum covered with sparse brown clavate and small dense plumose setae. Leg measurements: I 5.52 (1.78, 0.82, 1.31, 1.14, 0.47); II 4.80 (1.74, 0.73, 1.08, 0.86, 0.39); III 3.18 (0.95, 0.50, 0.80, 0.51, 0.42); IV 3.30 (1.24, 0.46, 0.74, 0.50, 0.36). Femora, patellae, and tibiae of legs I and II with dorsal outgrowths, especially long in distal parts of patellae. Spination: I Fe: d1, p4, v4; Pa: d3; Ti: d2, v8; Mt: r1, v8; II Fe: d3, v4; Pa: d2; Ti: d2, v8; Mt: v6; IV: Ti: d1, r1.
</paragraph>
<caption id="38D10BE4E0AE905E6CD21C84A782C022" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.72829.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672174" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" start="Figure 12" startId="F12">
<paragraph id="AACD05E1D19B0FA7AABD636E6C0AAD37" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="74CC47F6C204BE80A3B5447F5C685F54" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Figure 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BF80F5A1BAD5977B2ABEAEAFB9F06A78" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stephanopis xiangzhouica" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiangzhouica">
<emphasis id="B1F4FE52D1F67CFC63D2F634F37F6A57" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Stephanopis xiangzhouica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female holotype. 
<emphasis id="C30EDB34D4E4151E7A221F5C0D1405FF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">A</emphasis>
habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="2EBBD355DA09733F38B32BCBD7C43245" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">B</emphasis>
same, ventral view 
<emphasis id="709481B2F2EF55C4EBCF15710297932F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">C</emphasis>
cephalic part, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="24A3D9B63EFDE9F7052CF6F7AE22A8F0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">D</emphasis>
left chelicera, mesal view 
<emphasis id="830957D1A62525FF3C0E6776A431B3DB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">E</emphasis>
left leg I, prolateral view 
<emphasis id="7A02877C9D232470F66C3ED80EED73EE" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">F</emphasis>
patella I, prolateral view 
<emphasis id="D585F1A5EFD4C3616B721672DEFE39C2" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">G</emphasis>
abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars: 1 mm (
<emphasis id="2E8C726FF07C929B977F584B1AA160EF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">A, B</emphasis>
), 0.1 mm (
<emphasis id="DA48364EB3185F683C0EC4C9DBE18329" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">C, D, F</emphasis>
